This paper presents a geometric formulation of the Multiple Kernel Learning (MKL) problem, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper discusses optimization routines and scalability, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses empirical evaluation on datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses structural insights and geometric formulations, which could suggest it belongs to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses convergence and quality guarantees, which could suggest it belongs to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
